# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .dockerignore
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When Docker builds an image, it sends the entire "context" directory to the
# Docker daemon. This file tells Docker which files to SKIP, making builds
# faster and images smaller.
#
# Think of it like .gitignore but for Docker.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Node modules — each container installs its own (different OS, different arch)
**/node_modules

# Build output — dev containers don't need compiled JS
**/dist

# Git history — not needed inside containers
.git
.gitignore

# IDE and editor files
.vscode
.idea
**/.DS_Store

# Logs
**/logs
**/*.log

# Environment files are loaded via env_file in docker-compose, not COPY
# (But we do NOT ignore .env here because env_file references the path on host)

# Documentation
*.md
docs/
sprints/
high_level_architecture_final/

# Turborepo cache
.turbo
